Clearchus, a La­ cedæmonian, happened to be in exile.
Cyrus, having met with him, was struck with admiration for him, and made him a present of ten thousand darics.
2 Clearchus, on receiving the gold, raised, by means of it, a body of troops, and making ex­ cursions out of the Chersonesus, made war upon the Thracians that are situated above the Hellespont, and was of assist­ ance to the Greeks ;
so that the towns on the Hellespont willingly contributed money for the support of his men.
