who, however, would not go, but sending a messenger to Cyrus without the knowledge of the soldiers, bade him be of good courage, as these matters would be ar­ ranged to his satisfaction.
He also desired Cyrus to send for him again, but, when Cyrus had done so, he again declined to go.
