him, when he went, not only all the generals, but all the cap­ tains.
12. As they were all moved by the arguments of Seuthes, they joined him in an expedition, and proceeded through the country of the Thracians called Melinophagi, keeping the Euxine Sea on the right, to Salmydessus, Here many of the ships sailing into the Euxine are grounded and driven ashore ;
