"This also is to be enjoined on him who is trained to rule."
"And to which of the two would it more properly belong to acquire whatever knowledge would assist him to secure the mastery over his rivals?"
"Far more, doubtless, to him who is trained to govern, for without such sort of acquirements there would be no profit in any of his other qualifications."
