but myself I would number with those who wish to pass their lives in the greatest pos­ sible ease and pleasure."10.
Socrates then said, " Will you allow us to consider this point also, whether the governors or the governed live with the greater pleasure?" " By all means," said Aristippus. "
In the first place, then, of the nations of which we have any knowledge, the Persians bear rule in Asia, and the Syrians, Phrygians, and Lydians are under subjection ;
