you will raise your father's house, and increase the power of your country ;
you will be celebrated, first of all in your own city, and afterwards throughout Greece, and perhaps also, like Themistocles, among the Bar­ barians ;
and, wherever you may be, you will be an object of general admiration.”
3. Glaucon, hearing this, was highly elated, and cheerfully stayed to listen.
