" 4. But as Glaucon was silent, as if just considering how he should begin, Socrates said, " As, if you wished to aggran­ dize the family of a friend, you would endeavour to make it richer, tell me whether you will in like manner also endea­ vour to make the state richer ? " " Assuredly," said he.
