CONCERNING justice, too, he did not conceal what senti­ ments he entertained, but made them manifest even by his actions, for he conducted himself, in his private capacity, justly and beneficently towards all men, and, as a citizen, he obeyed the magistrates in all that the laws enjoined, both in the city and on military expeditions, so that lie was distin­ guished above other men for his observance of order.
